## Success Criteria

- **Batch 1 residency (leading):** At least 3 of 7 companies have active VC conversations within 60 days of demo day
- **Batch 1 residency (lagging):** At least 1 company raises EUR 500K+ within 9 months
- **Hackathon survival:** 30%+ of hackathon teams continue building after the event
- **Funnel conversion:** Evening → Hackathon (~10% of attendees apply), Hackathon → Residency (top 5-7 of 15 teams, ~30-50%)
- **Brand:** "One Evening. One Day. One Week." becomes recognizable positioning in European startup ecosystem
- **Revenue:** First non-sponsorship revenue (equity or participant fees) within 6 months

## Dependencies

- Secure a villa/venue for first residency batch
- Legal structure for equity agreements
- At least 2 hackathons run before first residency (to test selection)
- Continued VC sponsorship to fund operations
- Team bandwidth — need to understand who does what

## The Assignment

**Do not expand to any new city until you've run one full funnel cycle in Belgium.** Istanbul, Germany, Imperial — they'll wait. They reached out to you, which means demand exists. It won't disappear in 3 months.

Your one assignment: **Run your first hackathon within 6 weeks.** Not an evening — a full-day, selective, technical hackathon. This is the missing middle of your funnel. You know how to run evenings. You believe in the residency. The hackathon is the untested piece that connects them.

Get 15 teams. Make it selective. Track who keeps building after. Those people are your residency batch 1.

